<document>
  
  
  <properties>
    <title>CVS</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
        
        
        
          
                    <section name="Anonymous CVS Access">
        <p>
          This project's CVS repository can be checked out through anonymous (pserver)
          CVS with the following instruction set.
          When prompted for a password for anonymous, simply press the Enter key.
        </p>
      
        <p>
          cvs -d :pserver:jbrains@diasparsoftware.gotdns.com:/cvsroot/general login
          <br/>
          cvs -z3 -d :pserver:jbrains@diasparsoftware.gotdns.com:/cvsroot/general co DiasparsoftToolkit
        </p>

        <p>
          Updates from within the module's directory do not need the -d parameter.
        </p>
      </section>
              
              
          
      <section name="Developer CVS Access via SSH">

        <p>
          Only project developers can access the CVS tree via this method.
          SSH1 must be installed on your client machine. Substitute   
          <b>name</b> with the proper value. Enter your site password when prompted.
        </p>

        <p>
          export CVS_RSH=ssh
          <br/>
          cvs -z3 -d :pserver:username@diasparsoftware.gotdns.com:/cvsroot/general co DiasparsoftToolkit
        </p>
      
        <p>
          Remember to replace 'username' with your actual username on diasparsoftware.gotdns.com.
        </p>

      </section>
              
      
      </body>

</document>

